## Description {#details}

This class represents an assumption made on an AddRec expression.

Given an affine AddRec expression &#123;a,+,b&#125;, we assume that it has the nssw or nusw flags (defined below) in the first X iterations of the loop, where X is a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scev">SCEV</a> expression returned by getPredicatedBackedgeTakenCount).

Note that this does not imply that X is equal to the backedge taken count. This means that if we have a nusw predicate for i32 &#123;0,+,1&#125; with a predicated backedge taken count of X, we only guarantee that &#123;0,+,1&#125; has nusw in the first X iterations. &#123;0,+,1&#125; may still wrap in the loop if we have more than X iterations.

### enum  {#a0cfd938ff9c572d287e5e7923624db70}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum llvm::SCEVWrapPredicate::IncrementWrapFlags ">
Similar to <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scev/#af43000d4dcb7d6d63cb6e36933ed3f6f">SCEV::NoWrapFlags</a>, but with slightly different semantics for FlagNUSW.

<EnumerationListItem name="IncrementAnyWrap">

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a0cfd938ff9c572d287e5e7923624db70a17e825823d4b6a92c1b221c4460c91a3" />
<EnumerationListItem name="IncrementNUSW">
 (= (1 &lt;&lt; 0))
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a0cfd938ff9c572d287e5e7923624db70aa4c321f736f542d50b81bb06351f7fce" />
<EnumerationListItem name="IncrementNSSW">
 (= (1 &lt;&lt; 1))
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a0cfd938ff9c572d287e5e7923624db70a230598aea93080d7f8204727504352e7" />
<EnumerationListItem name="IncrementNoWrapMask">
 (= (1 &lt;&lt; 2) - 1)
</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

The increment is considered to be signed, and a + b (where b is the increment) is considered to wrap if: zext(a + b) != zext(a) + sext(b)

If Signed is a function that takes an n-bit tuple and maps to the integer domain as the tuples value interpreted as twos complement, and Unsigned a function that takes an n-bit tuple and maps to the integer domain as the base two value of input tuple, then a + b has IncrementNUSW iff:

0 &lt;= <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/nvptx/nvptxisellowering-cpp/#ae1a90b5d85643644483b2ca70da4d13fac837bff23a12c3735d463020f37979de">Unsigned(a)</a> + <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/nvptx/nvptxisellowering-cpp/#ae1a90b5d85643644483b2ca70da4d13faed3fa7a5efe80dad3ea3d86cc14be246">Signed(b)</a> &lt; 2^n

The IncrementNSSW flag has identical semantics with <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scev/#af43000d4dcb7d6d63cb6e36933ed3f6fa2f7a8775a783f7ea3ad24b3f9cb5d949">SCEV::FlagNSW</a>.

Note that the IncrementNUSW flag is not commutative: if base + inc has IncrementNUSW, then inc + base doesn&#39;t neccessarily have this property. The reason for this is that this is used for sign/zero extending affine AddRec <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scev">SCEV</a> expressions when a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scevwrappredicate">SCEVWrapPredicate</a> is assumed. A &#123;base,+,inc&#125; expression is already non-commutative with regards to base and inc, since it is interpreted as: (((base + inc) + inc) + inc) ...
